snippet.textDisplay: We’re probably gonna lose Aubameyang at the end of the season. He‘s a 20 plus goals per season striker. Imagine how much worse things would be if we didn’t have him or Lacazette. I remember a time after Henry left and Van Persie had not had a revelation due to lengthy injury spells when we didn’t have a 20 goals a season striker and had to rely on the likes of Jeremy Aliadiere and later Maruan Chamakh. It’s sad we’re talking our current strikers such as Aubameyang for granted.
